    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-07-18T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-07-18T21:00:00-05:00" n="416"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d416">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.3227/7–1844: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-18T22:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 18, 1944—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2210. On June 24 the Department, through an <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi>
                    to the Brazilian Embassy,<note n="53" xml:id="d416fn53">See footnote 35, <ref
                            target="#pg_494">p. 494</ref>.</note> invited the Brazilian Government
                    to participate in informal exploratory talks on post-war civil aviation. To date
                    no reply has been received.</p>
                <pb facs="0519" n="509" xml:id="pg_509"/>
                <p>Anything that you can discreetly and informally do to expedite acceptance of this
                    invitation and the commencement of the talks at an early date will be
                        helpful.<note n="54" xml:id="d416fn54">Ambassador Caffery in telegram 2826,
                        August 9, 1944, reported that he had, on the previous day, made inquiries of
                        the Brazilian Minister of Air, who stated that his principal officers had
                        under study the proposed exploratory talks on postwar civil aviation
                        (711.3227/8–944).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
